{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-tipping-content-js","path":"/serbia","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Tips are never considered a strict obligation since service charges are always included in the bill, however rounding up or leaving a tip (10-15%) is common in restaurants (not in fast-food restaurants) if the customer is satisfied with the service. Tips are also accepted in bars and taxicabs (usually by rounding up the amount paid - e.g. if the taximeter displays RSD 592, give 600).</p>","frontmatter":{"path":"/serbia","title":"Serbia","author":"Joni","date":"2019-11-22","image":"serbia.jpg"}},"image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.5,"src":"/static/24d8edc44ef7192722034e341efe36ff/90537/serbia.jpg","srcSet":"/static/24d8edc44ef7192722034e341efe36ff/b3ebb/serbia.jpg 270w,\n/static/24d8edc44ef7192722034e341efe36ff/95b54/serbia.jpg 540w,\n/static/24d8edc44ef7192722034e341efe36ff/90537/serbia.jpg 1080w,\n/static/24d8edc44ef7192722034e341efe36ff/3cda3/serbia.jpg 1620w,\n/static/24d8edc44ef7192722034e341efe36ff/1f682/serbia.jpg 2160w,\n/static/24d8edc44ef7192722034e341efe36ff/2728f/serbia.jpg 5184w","sizes":"(max-width: 1080px) 100vw, 1080px"}}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"image":"serbia.jpg"}}}